  {% include 'compare-backpacks-cta' %}

  <div class="more-window" id="magnets-overlay">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="title">Technical Information</h3>
      <p>Rare Earth magnets are electronic-safe and won’t damage modern technology like smartphones, laptops, CDs, or BluRays—they’re even found in cell phones, laptops, and tablets! You should, however, avoid letting them come in contact with “old” technology that has magnetic film, such as a first generation iPods, VHS tapes, and cassette tapes.</p>
      <p>Rare Earth magnets are nickel-free and Oeko-Tex-Certified, guaranteeing that they won’t cause skin irritation or allergic reactions. But keep in mind: Magnets should be kept away from pacemakers, scissors, knives, and needles. </p>
      <p>Do not attempt to iron or dry-clean magnets. </p>
    </div>
